### Register - weak password test
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users/register
Content-Type: application/json
X-Created-By: testuser

{
  "title": "MR",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User",
  "dateOfBirth": "1990-01-01",
  "email": "test.user@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+441234567890",
  "password": "weakpassword"
}

### Register admin user (requires ROLE_ADMIN token)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users/register/admin
Content-Type: application/json
X-Created-By: system
Authorization: Bearer <paste_admin_token_here>

{
  "title": "MS",
  "firstName": "Admin",
  "lastName": "User",
  "dateOfBirth": "1980-01-01",
  "email": "admin2@financehub.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+441234567892",
  "password": "Admin1!"
}

### ===================================
### GET ENDPOINTS
### ===================================

### Get all current users (admin only)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_admin_token_here>

### Get all users including inactive (admin only)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users?activeOnly=false
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_admin_token_here>

### Get user by ID (replace 1 with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

### Get user by email
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/email/john.smith@example.com
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

### Get user version history (replace 1 with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/1/history
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

### Get user at point in time (replace 1 with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/1/at?queryDate=2026-06-10T10:00:00
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

### ===================================
### SEARCH ENDPOINTS (admin only)
### ===================================

### Search by name wildcard
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/search?name=smi
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_admin_token_here>

### Search by first name only
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/search?firstName=john
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_admin_token_here>

### Search by last name only
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/search?lastName=smith
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_admin_token_here>

### Search by first and last name
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/search?firstName=john&lastName=smith
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_admin_token_here>

### Search including inactive users
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/search?name=smith&activeOnly=false
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_admin_token_here>

### Search - ambiguous parameters test
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/search?name=john&firstName=john
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_admin_token_here>

### ===================================
### UPDATE ENDPOINTS
### ===================================

### Update user (replace 1 with actual ID)
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json
X-Updated-By: testuser
Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

{
  "title": "DR",
  "firstName": "John",
  "middleName": "William",
  "lastName": "Smith",
  "dateOfBirth": "1985-06-15",
  "email": "john.smith@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "+441234567890",
  "password": "Password1!"
}

### Verify email (replace 1 with actual ID)
PATCH http://localhost:8081/api/users/1/verify-email
Content-Type: application/json
X-Updated-By: testuser
Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

### Update status (admin only - replace 1 with actual ID)
PATCH http://localhost:8081/api/users/1/status?status=ACTIVE
Content-Type: application/json
X-Updated-By: testuser
Authorization: Bearer <paste_admin_token_here>

### Reinstate deleted user (admin only - replace 1 with actual ID)
PATCH http://localhost:8081/api/users/1/reinstate
Content-Type: application/json
X-Updated-By: admin
Authorization: Bearer <paste_admin_token_here>

### ===================================
### PASSWORD ENDPOINTS
### ===================================

### Change password (replace 1 with actual ID)
PATCH http://localhost:8081/api/users/1/change-password
Content-Type: application/json
X-Updated-By: testuser
Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

{
  "currentPassword": "Password1!",
  "newPassword": "NewPassword1!"
}

### Change password - wrong current password test
PATCH http://localhost:8081/api/users/1/change-password
Content-Type: application/json
X-Updated-By: testuser
Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

{
  "currentPassword": "WrongPassword1!",
  "newPassword": "NewPassword1!"
}

### Change password - previously used password test
PATCH http://localhost:8081/api/users/1/change-password
Content-Type: application/json
X-Updated-By: testuser
Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

{
  "currentPassword": "NewPassword1!",
  "newPassword": "Password1!"
}

### Request password reset
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users/password-reset/request
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.smith@example.com"
}

### Confirm password reset (paste token from above response)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users/password-reset/confirm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resetToken": "paste-token-here",
  "newPassword": "Password1!"
}

### Confirm password reset - expired/invalid token test
POST http://localhost:8081/api/users/password-reset/confirm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "resetToken": "invalid-token-12345",
  "newPassword": "Password1!"
}

### ===================================
### DELETE ENDPOINT
### ===================================

### Soft delete user (replace 1 with actual ID)
DELETE http://localhost:8081/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json
X-Deleted-By: testuser
Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

### Verify user deleted - should return 404
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

### Get history after delete - should show closed record
GET http://localhost:8081/api/users/1/history
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <paste_token_here>

